<item>
            <title>[HBASE-3259] Can&apos;t kill the region servers when they wait on the master or the cluster state znode</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3259</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With a situation like &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3258&quot; title=&quot;EOF when version file is empty&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3258&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3258&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, it&apos;s easy to have the region servers stuck on waiting for either the master or the cluster state znode since it has no timeout. You have to kill -9 them to have them shutting down. This is very bad for usability.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12480603">HBASE-3259</key>
            <summary>Can&apos;t kill the region servers when they wait on the master or the cluster state znode</summary>
